        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 8:38PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 838 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Cedar Creek, or near
Abbeville, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Abbeville, Rochelle, Pineview, Pitts, Union, Cedar Creek, Antioch
Church, Pope City, Ocmulgee Banks, and Finleyson.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
